## Shotcaller — Route to Market Summary

---

**The product:**
Shotcaller as an offline-only PWA (Progressive Web App). Installs on Mac, Windows, and iPad like a native app. Works without internet — which is a genuine feature for live production environments with unreliable venue wifi.

---

**Why offline-only makes sense:**

- No backend to build or maintain
- No monthly server costs
- No auth system needed
- Simpler, faster, more reliable for the environment it's used in

---

**How you sell it:**
One-time purchase through WooCommerce on your existing wannesvideo.com WordPress site.

- WooCommerce is free
- Stripe plugin for WooCommerce is free
- Stripe takes their standard % per transaction
- You issue Belgian VAT invoices through WooCommerce as you normally would through your BV
- Your existing BTW registration covers EU VAT compliance
- Customer pays, automatically receives a license key by email

---

**License key system:**

- Keys generated by a small PHP snippet on your WordPress server using a secret you hold
- Customer enters the key once in the app on first launch
- App validates it locally using HMAC — no server call needed
- Key stored in localStorage permanently after activation
- Limitation: no machine limit enforcement, but acceptable for a professional market at this price point

---

**What needs to be built:**

| Item | Effort | Cost |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Convert app to PWA | 1 Claude Code session | €0 |
| License activation screen in app | 1 Claude Code session | €0 |
| License validation logic in app | Same session as above | €0 |
| WooCommerce setup | 1–2 hours | €0 |
| PHP key generator snippet | 1 Claude Code session | €0 |
| License manager plugin (optional, for automation) | — | ~€50 one-time |
| Stripe plugin for WooCommerce | — | €0 |

---

**Pricing recommendation:**
One-time purchase. €149–199 for an individual license. €249 for a studio license (multiple installs). Fits the freelance AD and production company buyer who thinks per-show, not per-month.

---

**Total monthly cost to run:**
€0 — assuming wannesvideo.com is already on WordPress hosting you're paying for anyway.

---

**The only things standing between the current app and a paid product:**

1. PWA conversion — makes it installable and offline-capable
2. License key system — activation screen + validation + WordPress key generator
3. WooCommerce product page — the actual shop listing
4. A landing page — explaining what it does, who it's for, with a buy button

Everything else is already built.